    "body": "Launch the debugger, and it immediately aborts. The logs say\n\n```\n$ cat target/osdk-miri/os-miri-base/miri-debugger.log\nDebugger exited with error:\nCustom { kind: Other, error: Custom { kind: Other, error: \"The cursor position could not be read within a normal duration\" } }\n\n$ cat target/osdk-miri/os-miri-base/miri_diagnostics.txt\nwarning: unstable feature specified for `-Ctarget-feature`: `ermsb`\n  |\n  = note: this feature is not stably supported; its behavior can change in the future\n\nerror: interpretation was interrupted\n  --> src/main.rs:15:9\n   |\n15 |     let args = unsafe { core::slice::from_raw_parts(argv, argc as usize) };\n   |         ^^^^ error occurred here\n\nerror: aborting due to 1 previous error; 1 warning emitted\n```\n\nThe reason is  calls like read and poll  are not allowed in different threads as per https://docs.rs/crossterm/latest/crossterm/event/index.html .",
